        where
        x
        is the input,
        pi
        is the
        i
        -th paragraph in the Wikipedia collection,
        œï‚Å¢(pi)
        is the term vector extracted from
        pi
        .
The term vector for the input
        x
        ,
        œï‚Å¢(x)
        , is computed by accumulating the weights in the previous turns as follows:
       </p>
